-- Phillies Defeat Cincinnati Reds 2-0, Sweep Three-Game NL Playoff Series
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2010-10-11T03:08:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/phillies-defeat-reds-2-0-sweep-three-game-national-league-playoff-series.html
Cole Hamels pitched a five hitter
and Chase Utley hit a solo home run as the Philadelphia Phillies
won 2-0 to complete a three-game sweep of the host Cincinnati
Reds in the National League playoffs.  Philadelphia advanced to the NL Championship Series to face
either the San Francisco Giants or Atlanta Braves. The Giants
have a 2-1 lead in their division series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  